    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a preserved example of naturally aspirated excellence. Powered by the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, the engine utilizes individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure dual-VANOS system to deliver a razor-sharp throttle response and a soaring 8,000 RPM redline. Power is channeled through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to the rear wheels via a factory M-Variable differential lock. The chassis remains impeccably rigid, with the rear subframe professionally reinforced and the suspension components maintaining original factory tolerances. The exterior features flawless paint depth with no oxidation or swirl marks, while the interior Nappa leather retains its original matte finish and bolster integrity. This is a turn-key, investment-grade vehicle that offers a pure mechanical connection, free from the electronic interference of modern counterparts.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Low mileage. No accidents. Clean title. Garage kept. Inspection welcome.",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "Presenting a truly exceptional specimen that defines showroom quality. This vehicle has been meticulously maintained in a climate-controlled environment, preserving its factory-fresh appearance and performance. The exterior features a deep, mirror-like finish with zero paint chips, swirls, or dings, further protected by a premium multi-stage ceramic coating that makes the color pop. Inside, the cabin remains in pristine condition; the leather upholstery is supple and completely free of bolster wear or creasing, while the carpets have been protected by original floor mats since day one. Mechanically, this car is beyond reproach, boasting a comprehensive service history documented in a thick binder of receipts. Every button, switch, and electronic component functions exactly as it did the day it left the assembly line. The engine bay is remarkably clean, reflecting the preventative maintenance schedule followed religiously by its sole adult owner. Included in the sale are all original keys, the factory window sticker, and a clean title. This is a rare opportunity to own a collector-grade vehicle that looks and drives as if it just rolled off the showroom floor. Professional inspections are welcomed and encouraged.",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
